val dataTemp = sqlContext.read
    .format("com.databricks.spark.csv")
    .option("header", "true") // Use first line of all files as header
    .option("inferSchema", "true") // Automatically infer data types
    .option("delimiter", ",")
    .load("/data/sidana/recnet_draft/kasandr/cofactor/ratings.csv")

val positiveData = dataTemp.filter($"rating">=4)
val usersPositiveOffers = positiveData.select("userId","movieId").distinct
val userPositiveClickCount = usersPositiveOffers.groupBy("userId").count
val goodUsers = userPositiveClickCount.filter($"count">=2)


val negativeData =  dataTemp.filter($"rating"<=1)
val usersNegativeOffers = negativeData.select("userId","movieId").distinct
val userNegativeClickCount = usersNegativeOffers.groupBy("userId").count
val badUsers = userNegativeClickCount.filter($"count">=10)


val goodDataTemp = dataTemp.join(goodUsers,dataTemp("userId")===goodUsers("userId")).drop(goodUsers("count")).drop(goodUsers("userId"))
val goodBadDataTemp = goodDataTemp.join(badUsers,goodDataTemp("userId")===badUsers("userId")).drop(badUsers("count")).drop(badUsers("userId"))

val goodData = goodBadDataTemp.select("userId","movieId","rating","timestamp")
goodData.rdd.coalesce(1,false).saveAsTextFile("/data/sidana/recnet_draft/kasandr/atleast_ten_o_two_c/ratings_temp.csv")
